<b><big><a name="Description">Description</a></big></b>
<br/>
This is an extension of the
<a href="nearequal.xml" target="_top"><span style='white-space: nowrap'>NearEqual</span></a>
 routine to more cases.
It returns true if 

<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><mrow>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
<mspace width='.3em'/>
<mrow><mstyle mathvariant='normal'><mi mathvariant='normal'>or</mi>
</mstyle></mrow>
<mspace width='.3em'/>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">-</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mo stretchy="false">&#x02264;</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>a</mi>
<mspace width='.3em'/>
<mrow><mstyle mathvariant='normal'><mi mathvariant='normal'>or</mi>
</mstyle></mrow>
<mspace width='.3em'/>
<mfrac><mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">-</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
</mrow>
<mrow><mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>x</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mo stretchy="false">+</mo>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>y</mi>
<mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
</mrow>
</mfrac>
<mo stretchy="false">&#x02264;</mo>
<mi mathvariant='italic'>r</mi>
</mrow></math>

Otherwise, it return false.
Note that <i>a</i> is an absolute error bound
and <i>r</i> is a relative error bound.



